post_text: Friends and families of GEO Prep Academy, Iâ€™m writing to share that we are aware of the challenges regarding the availability of chromebooks at home. We are working on getting more chromebooks with the goal of having one chromebook to each student, no matter how many live in the same house. With the challenge of teachers across grade levels having to teach at the same time and/or conflicting times, sharing a chromebook between siblings is not the best solution. We hope to be able to share great news with you in a day or so. Hang in there and be safe.

Interesting reactions to coronavirus. In Indiana, a state with 12 confirmed cases, the Governor gave schools the option to close for up to 20 days. Louisiana has 14 cases and the Governor ordered all schools statewide shut down for a month. In California, where there are 247 cases and 5 deaths, my nieceâ€™s school is closed for a week. She lives near the Princess cruise ship, too. And in NYC, where there are 154 cases, the Mayor of NYC orders all public schools to remain open. Wow!

Stay safe!

post_text:
Dear Baton Rouge families,

Due to the coronavirus threat facing our community, in compliance with Gov. John Bel Edward's proclamation, our GEO Academy schools will be closing down as of today, and will re-open no sooner than April 13, 2020.

Our students will be bringing home their "learn from home" packets today, with 10 school days' worth of learning material, and our teachers will be ready to support them over the next weeks as we all adjust to our new learning environment. As you know, this situation is changing quickly, and we will continue to update you as new information becomes available.

We are working with our food provider to continue to provide breakfast and lunch meals for pick up at our school sites. We will have more information available for you on that program soon.

Be well and stay safe,
Kevin Teasley, Superintendent
GEO Academies
text:
Dear Baton Rouge families,

Due to the coronavirus threat facing our community, in compliance with Gov. John Bel Edward's proclamation, our GEO Academy schools will be closing down as of today, and will re-open no sooner than April 13, 2020.

Our students will be bringing home their "learn from home" packets today, with 10 school days' worth of learning material, and our teachers will be ready to support them over the next weeks as we all adjust to our new learning environment. As you know, this situation is changing quickly, and we will continue to update you as new information becomes available.

We are working with our food provider to continue to provide breakfast and lunch meals for pick up at our school sites. We will have more information available for you on that program soon.

Be well and stay safe,
Kevin Teasley, Superintendent
GEO Academies

So excited to share our recent successes! Thanks to a great team and great families!

3 (nearly 4) of 5 tested grades are in the top 1% of the country for growth in reading, the other two are in top 27% and 11%.

3 of 3 tested grades are in the top 10% of the country in growth for language arts, two are at top 1% in the country.

3 of 5 tested grades are in the top 1% in math growth, and the other two are in top 11% and top 5%. WOW!!!

post_text:
Hey Friends of GEO Prep,

Just a few days ago, a state court ruled that Type 2 Charter schools (means schools like GEO Prep Academy) could no longer receive state funding http://www.wwltv.com/news/court-ruling-affects-funding-for-over-30-charter-schools/385068783. GEO Prep Academy survives on state funding--because we are a FREE, PUBLIC charter school, that serves ALL students. We don't pick and choose students.

Please contact your legislators today and ask them to speak out on your behalf and express their disagreement with this law. GEO Prep being able to continue to serve students in Baton Rouge depends on it. Find your legislator here : http://www.legis.la.gov/legis/FindMyLegislators.aspx
shared_text:
WWLTV.COM
Court ruling could affect funding for over 30 charter schools
text:
Hey Friends of GEO Prep,

GEO Prep Academy survives on state funding--because we are a FREE, PUBLIC charter school, that serves ALL students. We don't pick and choose students.

Please contact your legislators today and ask them to speak out on your behalf and express their disagreement with this law. GEO Prep being able to continue to serve students in Baton Rouge depends on it. Find your legislator here : http://www.legis.la.gov/legis/FindMyLegislators.aspx
